ties the trading of currencies and commodities equities the trading of equities equity derivatives structured products options and futures contracts and principal investments merchant banking investments and funds this segment consists of the revenues and profit gained from the banks trading activities both on behalf of its clients known as flow trading and for its own account known as proprietary trading investment managementedit in  investment management accounted for  of total company revenues the investment management division provides investment advisory and financial planning services and offers investment products primarily through separately managed accounts and commingled vehicles across all major asset classes to a diverse group of institutions and individuals worldwide the division provides clearing financing custody securities lending and reporting services to institutional clients including hedge funds mutual funds and pension funds the division generates revenues primarily in the form of spreads or management and transaction fees gs capital partnersedit main article goldman sachs capital partners gs capital partners is the private equity arm of goldman sachs that invests on behalf of institutional clients it has invested over  billion in the  years from  to  one of the most prominent funds is the gs capital partners v fund which has over  billion of equity for investment on april   goldman closed new investment in gs capital partners vi with  billion in committed capital including  billion from qualified institutional and highnetworth clients and  billion from goldman sachs and its employees in  the company announced it will raise up to  billion for a new fund focused on corporate buyouts its first new fund since the financial crisis of  investments owned by goldman sachs funds include american casino  entertainment properties  of eaglebank  of chinese meat processor shuanghui transunion and  of cmc markets corporate citizenshipedit see also goldman sachs foundation according to its website goldman sachs has committed in excess of  billion to philanthropic initiatives since  goldman sachs reports its environmental and social performance in an annual corporate social responsibility csr report that follows the global reporting initiative gri protocol goldman sachs global leaders programedit during  the goldman sachs global leaders program gsglp identified  exceptional undergraduate students from  participating universities and colleges around the globe awarded them global leaders in recognition of their academic excellence and leadership potential global leaders study a diverse range of fields from economics to medical science gsglp alumni have gone on to win rhodes truman marshall gates and cambridge scholarships and fulbright fellowships climate change policiesedit goldman sachs has received favorable press coverage for conducting business and implementing internal policies related to reversing global climate change the company has invested  billion in the clean energy sector since  with the goal of investing  billion by  goldman sachs has helped tesla motors raise  billion employee contributionsedit goldman sachs givesedit in november  goldman sachs established a donor advised fund called goldman sachs gives that donates to charitable organizations around the world and providing an employee donation match of up to  community teamworksedit the firms community teamworks is an annual global volunteering initiative that gives  goldman employees a day off work from may through august to volunteer in a teambased project organized with a local nonprofit organization the initiative has worked on  projects for  organizations junior banker task forceedit in  goldman sachs developed a junior banker task force of executives from around the world to improve analysts work environment and career development  womenedit in march  goldman launched the  women initiative to train  women from predominantly developing countries in bu