 merely said that the cdos contents were assets sourced from the street making it sound as though goldman randomly selected the securities instead of specifically creating a hedge for its won book   bethany mclean joe nocera all the devils are here the hidden history of the financial crisis p    bethany mclean joe nocera all the devils are here the hidden history of the financial crisis pp –   nathaniel popper april   main st paid for wall st maneuvers los angeles times   wang marian april   banks pressured credit agencies then blamed them propublica   a b lucchetti aaron ng serena april   abacus deal as bad as they come the wall street journal   a b c whalen philip tan bhala kara goldman sachs and the abacus deal seven pillars institute   a b wilchins dan april   factbox how goldmans abacus deal worked april   reuters retrieved february   hedge fund manager john paulson tells goldman sachs in late  he wants to bet against risky subprime mortgages using derivatives the risky mortgage bonds that paulson wanted to short were essentially subprime home loans that had been repackaged into bonds the bonds were rated bbb meaning that as the home loans defaulted these bonds would be among the first to feel the pain   the  million has been described as rent for the abacus name bethany mclean joe nocera all the devils are here the hidden history of the financial crisis p  paulson knocked on goldmans door at a fortuitous moment the firm had begun thinking about abacusrenal strategies  by that he meant that goldman would rent—for a hefty fee—the abacus brand to a hedge fund that wanted to make a massive short bet  paulson paid goldman  million to rent the abacus name   goldmans misleading statement on aca reuters april   when goldman wrapped the supersenior tranche of the abacus deal it did so with abn amro a toobigtofail bank and not with aca abn amro then laid off that risk onto aca but was on the hook for all of it if aca went bust as of course it did   a b c securities and 